{"lemma":"أَخْضَرِ","slug":"أَخْضَرِ","root":"خ.ض.ر","root_slug":"خ-ض-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ض-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَخْضَر","root":"خضر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10866","n10868","n10888"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"green; verdant"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dark; black","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"gray","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from root خ ض ر (ḵ ḍ r)."},"ipa":["/ʔax.dˤar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10866","headword_ar":"اخضر","root":"xDr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(plenty of moisture)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered"},{"kind":"text","text":"seedproduce"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n10868","headword_ar":"اخضرّ","root":"xDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixoDiraArN","text_ar":"اِخْضِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDwDr","text_ar":"اخضوضر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixoDiyDaArN","text_ar":"اِخْضِيضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the TA written by mistake"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixoDiyraArN","text_ar":"اِخْضِيرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDira","text_ar":"حَضِرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDarN","text_ar":"خَضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a colour, Msb, or seed-produce, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel, and a horse, and an ass, and sometimes a bird,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like, or any other thing,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dingy ash-colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark dust-colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, of a tawny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brownish, colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a blackish hue inclining to green;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorapN","text_ar":"خُضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, A, Msb, K.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~ A_izaAraY","text_ar":"اخضرّ اـِزَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AzAr","text_ar":"ازار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, rather,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became of a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackish"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hue inclining to green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the hair when it first grows is of that hue. (Har p. 494.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~ $aAribuhu","text_ar":"اخضرّ شَارِبُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His mustache grew so as to appear dark"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said of a boy; a phrase similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqala wajohuhu","text_ar":"بَقَلَ وَجْهُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bql","text_ar":"بقل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~All~ayolu","text_ar":"اخضرّاللَّيْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The night became dark and black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~t AlZ~ulomapu","text_ar":"اخضرّت الظُّلْمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The darkness became intensely black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~ jilodatuhu","text_ar":"اخضرّ جِلْدَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His skin became green"},{"kind":"text","text":"from carrying the produce of his land; meaning] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became in a state of plenty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo xuDoru AlmanaAkibi","text_ar":"هُمْ خُضْرُ المَنَاكِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~","text_ar":"اخضرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of seed-produce,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDwDr","text_ar":"اخضوضر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDira","text_ar":"خَضِرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDarN","text_ar":"خَضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr~","text_ar":"اخضرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixotaDara","text_ar":"اِخْتَضَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this may be of the pass. form, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuxotuDira","text_ar":"اُخْتُضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] so as to agree with what occurs before, [see 8,] (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(herbage, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, cut."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10888","headword_ar":"اَخْضَرُ","root":"xDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Green; verdant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuD~aAraY","text_ar":"خُضَّارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDirN","text_ar":"خَضِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDiyrN","text_ar":"خَضِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDuwrN","text_ar":"خَضُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoDuwrN","text_ar":"يَخْضُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxoDiyrN","text_ar":"يَخْضِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA: the last two written in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoDuwrN","text_ar":"تَخْضُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoDiyrN","text_ar":"تَخْضِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) applied to a horse, [and to a camel, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorapN","text_ar":"خُضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and to an ass, and sometimes to a bird, and to a garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like, and to various other things,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dingy ash-colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark dust-colour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dust-colour intermixed with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhomap","text_ar":"دُهْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deep ash-colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; which is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayozajN","text_ar":"دَيْزَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) in horses being distinguished as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru A^adogamu","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ اَدْغَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru A^aToHalu","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ اَطْحَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru A^aworaqu","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ اَوْرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA: [see the latter epithet in each of these cases:]) applied to a man, [and to other things,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tawny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brownish:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blackish:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a blackish hue inclining to green:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black-complexioned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intensely black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said in the Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Htm","text_ar":"حتم"},{"kind":"text","text":", that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, with the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which may mean either that green is, with the Arabs, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aswd","text_ar":"اسود"},{"kind":"text","text":", or that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAxDr","text_ar":"الاخضر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is, with the Arabs, black: but the truth is, that each of the epithets"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used for the other: see what here follows, and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in Har p. 495, it is erroneously said, on the authority of Er-Rázee, that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aswd","text_ar":"اسود"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not termed by the Arabs"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr","text_ar":"اخضر"},{"kind":"text","text":", although the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxDr","text_ar":"اخضر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed by them"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aswd","text_ar":"اسود"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its intense"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riY~","text_ar":"رِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorN","text_ar":"خُضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapN xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"شَجَرَةٌ خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A green, and fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"juicy, tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N A^axoDaru","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water inclining to a green colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of its clearness. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru Aljilodapi","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ الجِلْدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tawny of skin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of pure race;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the complexions of the Arabs are tawny; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of genuine Arab race:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB:) as in the saying of El-Lahabee, (S, TA,) El-Fadl Ibn-'Abbás, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^anaA AlA^axoDaru mano yaEorifuniY\n                      \n                     \n                        A^axoDaru Aljilodapi fiY bayoti AlEarabo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I am the tawny: who knows me? the tawny of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or pure of race"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the family that comprises the nobility of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, IB.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^axoDaru AlqafaA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَخْضَرُ القَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is blackish, or black, in the back of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is the son of a black woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, A:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is slapped on the back of his neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a freedman, or an emancipated slave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru AlbaToni","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ البَطْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A weaver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) because his belly, being stuck close to his loom, becomes blackened by it. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru Aln~awaAji*i","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ النَّوَاجِذِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An eater of onions and leeks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tiller,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivator, of the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because he eats herbs, or leguminous plants. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo xuDoru AlmanaAkibi","text_ar":"هُمْ خُضْرُ المَنَاكِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are green in the shoulders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from carrying the produce of their land:] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are in a state of great plenty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And [hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one possesses abundant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayor","text_ar":"خَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) [or it may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, is an epithet of praise, whereby he may be likened to the sea, because it is described as green, or to the [rain or herbage called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in both cases meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal, or bountiful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is so applied because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorapN","text_ar":"خُضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the colours of the Arabs: and it is also an epithet of dispraise, as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black by reason of baseness, ignobleness, or meanness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 282.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAb~N A^axoDaru","text_ar":"شَابٌّ اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young man whose hair has begun to grow upon the sides of his face."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katiybapN xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"كَتِيبَةٌ خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a troop of horse, overspread with the blackness of iron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great army or troop of horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which most of the men are clad in iron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA^owaA='u","text_ar":"جَاْوَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) because of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the iron: (A:) [i. e.] because of the blackness thereof. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayolu A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اللَّيْلُ اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Night is black."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jan~a Ealayohi A^axoDaru AljanaAHayoni","text_ar":"جَنَّ عَلَيْهِ اَخْضَرُ الجَنَاحَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Night"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the black-winged"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veiled him, concealed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covered him with its darkness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudohaAm~ataAni","text_ar":"مُدْهَامَّتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lv. 64, relating to two gardens of Paradise], is explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraAwaAni","text_ar":"خَضْرَاوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inclining to blackness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of abundance of moisture, or irrigation. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a subst.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDaArapN","text_ar":"خُضَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  The fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is also used as a subst., and] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gree herbs or leguminous plants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDaArapN","text_ar":"خُضَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraAwaAtN","text_ar":"خَضْرَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorN","text_ar":"خُضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but as the quality of a subst. predominates in it, it has a pl. like the pl. of a subst., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHoraAwaAtN","text_ar":"صَحْرَاوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHoraA='N","text_ar":"صَحْرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) this pl. occurs in the saying (in a trad., TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa fiY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDoraAwaAti SadaqapN","text_ar":"الخَضْرَاوَاتِ صَدَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no poor-rate in the case of green herbs or leguminous plants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh fruits and herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the apple and the pear &c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as leeks and smallage and rue and the like; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDarN","text_ar":"خُضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorapN","text_ar":"خُضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is sometimes substituted for it. (Mgh.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAkumo waxaDoraA='u Ald~imani","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكُمْ وَخَضْرَا=ءُ الدِّمَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Avoid ye the beautiful woman that is of bad origin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb:) because what grows in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimonap","text_ar":"دِمْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or place which men have blackened by their cooking, and where their camels or other beasts have staled and dunged], though it may be beautiful and bright, does not bear fruit [because it is neglected, and left unwatered], (S, Msb,) and soon becomes corrupt, or bad. (Msb. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimonapN","text_ar":"دِمْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$obapN Ald~aAri","text_ar":"عُشْبَةٌ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$b","text_ar":"عشب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDoraA='u","text_ar":"الخَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heaven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) because of its greenness; like as the earth is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgaboraA='u","text_ar":"الغَبْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA taHota AlxaDoraA='i A^akorahu minohu","text_ar":"مَا تَحْتَ الخَضْرَا=ءِ اَكْرَهُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not under the sky one more hateful than he"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which water has been drawn long, so that it has become green or blackish"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY A@xoDar~ato","text_ar":"حَتَّى ا@خْضَرَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"congregated or collective body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people. (S, K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAda A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"اَبَادَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='ahumo","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God destroy the congregated or collective body, mass, or bulk, of them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or this means, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their stock"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarap","text_ar":"شَجَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which they have branched off;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their life in this present world:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their enjoyment and plenty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plenty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enjoyment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in a later part of this art.:) or the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaDoraA='ahumo","text_ar":"غَضْرَا=ءَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning “their prosperity, and their pleasantness of life, or plenty and prosperity.” (S. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gDr","text_ar":"غضر"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqolapu AlxaDoraA='u","text_ar":"البَقْلَةُ الخَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDirN","text_ar":"خَضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuDoru","text_ar":"الخُضْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaDoraA='u","text_ar":"الخَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The domestic pigeons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) so called although of various colours, because their predominant colour is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuroqap","text_ar":"وُرْقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ash-colour], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning a dark, or an ashy, dust-colour]: the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDor","text_ar":"خُضْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numor","text_ar":"نُمْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or spotted with white and black, &c.,] are especially characterized by the faculty of rightly directing their course. (T, TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axaASiru","text_ar":"الاَخَاصِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a subst.] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold and flesh-meat and wine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHaAmirapu","text_ar":"الاَحَامِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as some explain this latter]. (TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoDaru","text_ar":"اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amoru bayonanaA A^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَمْرُ بَيْنَنَا اَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair between us is fresh, or recent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawad~apu bayonanaA xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"المَوَدَّةُ بَيْنَنَا خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection, between us is fresh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tender;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to herbage, or seed-produce. (TA.) ―         -b11-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiy$apN xaDoraA='u","text_ar":"عِيشَةٌ خَضْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode of life soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delicate, and plentiful and pleasant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 639.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^axoDaru","text_ar":"الاَخْضَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism;"},{"kind":"text","text":"most probably either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a of Piscis Australis"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ε","text_ar":"ε","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Pegasus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some star or asterism nearly in a line with those two;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anowaA='","text_ar":"اَنْوَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the rain called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxariyf","text_ar":"الخَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"; namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the middle"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'","text_ar":"نَوْء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those three"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnwA='","text_ar":"انوا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the first being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoraAni","text_ar":"نَسْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the last, the foremost of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farogaAni","text_ar":"فَرْغَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AZ, T and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwA^","text_ar":"نوا"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","TA","IB","Az","A","Fr","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}